    <bioghist encodinganalog="545$a">
      <head>Historical Information
</head>
      <p>Essex County was formed from Old Rappahannock County in 1692.  Its area is 261 square miles, and the county seat is Tappahannock.
</p>
    
   </bioghist>
    <scopecontent encodinganalog="520$a">
      <head>Scope and Content
</head>
      <p>Essex County (Va.) Sheriff Tax Collection Books, 1811, 1815, is the rough draft of land, personal property, slave property, and other taxes owed and collected.  Also included in the volumes were other fees collected by the sheriff.
</p>
